thank you for supporting legal education and equal access to justice  yes you can share our videos on your social media networks  

what is willful copyright infringement  click to knowledgeup

in this video you will learn about the legal definition of willful copyright infringement  as you will see this term can encompass many different types of actions such as

1  intentional infringement

2  knowing infringement

3  reckless disregard of a copyright owners rights

4  allegations of willfulness in a complaint lawsuit that are not responded to and accepted as true in entering a default judgment

the opposite of willful infringement is innocent infringement  this can make a big difference when you are dealing with a plaintiff who has registered copyright seeking up to 150000 per infringed work for willful infringement versus much less if the piracy was innocent accidental not knowing or negligent

title: what the new copyright claims board means for creators
description:
the copyright claims board ccb is a newly established tribunal within the united states copyright office that offers a voluntary alternative to the federal district courts for certain lowvalue copyright disputes the product of years of hearings and debates among various stakeholders the ccb provides affordable streamlined procedures designed to ensure that all creators have meaningful and effective tools to protect their rights please join hudson institute legal fellow devlin hartline and expert panelists maya burchette terrica carrington and michael klipper for a panel discussion on the ccbs legislative and historical background administration and functionality and meaning for everyday creators

description:
susanna hs leong professor of law at the nus business school national university of singapore spoke on the topic of internet intermediaries and copyright infringement  who makes the copy at a seminar on 9 november 2017 

susanna hs leong is a professor of law at the nus business school national university of singapore and is an advocate  solicitor of the supreme court of singapore susanna received her llb hons from national university of singapore and her llm with merit from university college london university of london she teaches business related law courses such as contract sale of goods and intellectual property to undergraduate and graduate business students in english and chinese her research interests are in intellectual property and technologyrelated laws she has published in several international and local academic journals she is also the author of intellectual property law of singapore academy publishing singapore

susanna was the vicedean graduate studies nus business school january 2008 to december 2016 she is a senior fellow at the intellectual property academy of singapore she is a member of wipo arbitration and mediation centres domain name panel a member of the regional centre for arbitration kuala lumpur rcakl panel and a member of asian domain name dispute resolution centre hong kong she is also a member of the singapore copyright tribunal

title: how to submit a fair use copyright claim dispute in youtube april 2023
description:
cole powell is an awardwinning singersongwriter from jayess mississippi usa ie he is definitely not a lawyer and those who implement the procedure demonstrated in this video do so at their own risk  tutorial starts  0044

randomine records patreon httpswwwpatreoncomuseru84314605

how to appeal a fair use copyright claim rejection on youtube httpswwwyoutubecomwatchvuarksfyxalmt78s

our dispute rationale as of feb 4 2024 

the video which has been flagged for containing copyrighted material is a music reaction video which follows the general format of many similar videos currently widely available on youtube the copyrightclaimed material features in the original video that serves as the subject of the reaction 
 
this original video has been reduced in size by 64 while its audio volume level has also been reduced the original video is also stopped and removed from the screen multiple times throughout the reaction video while blocks of commentary on the original video content are being delivered commentary is also occasionally delivered while the original video is playing obscuring some of the original videos audio 

the purpose of this reaction video is to offer analysis and critique of the music and performance featured in the original video with the reactor offering a unique perspective as a singer songwriter and musician 

also please note that the video containing the copyrighted material in question is and will remain unpublished pending clearance through this fair use claim

title: understanding dmca takedown notices a global guide for artists creators entrepreneurs and bus
description:
in todays digital world where content can be shared and reshared with a single click protecting your intellectual property has become more important than ever but what do you do when someone uses your work without permission enter the digital millennium copyright act dmca and the dmca takedown noticean essential tool for anyone looking to protect their copyrighted content online in this episode were breaking down everything you need to know about dmca takedown notices
 

well start with the basicswhat exactly is a dmca takedown notice and how does it work then well walk you through the legal requirements to make sure your notice is ironclad well also provide a stepbystep template that you can use to send your own dmca takedown notice in all 50 states
 

but it doesnt stop there well explore what happens if the infringing party doesnt comply how to escalate your claim and what legal remedies you can pursue including actual damages and statutory penalties plus well dive into the nuances of dealing with international copyright laws and how different countries handle dmcalike regulations
 

whether youre an artist creator entrepreneur or business owner this episode will equip you with the knowledge and tools to protect your work enforce your rights and navigate the complex world of online copyright infringement

title: bill gates snow ball fight
description:
bill gates snow day shocker billionaires bizarre video sparks online frenzy

in a surprising twist thats left the internet buzzing billionaire tech mogul bill gates dropped an unexpected video on social media trading his usual serious tone for a playful moment in the snow you cant let a seattle snow day go to waste he quipped showing off a rare glimpse of the microsoft cofounder enjoying a snowy day in his hometown seattle not exactly known for blizzardlevel weather saw some light snow in early february 2025enough to disrupt local routines and apparently inspire gates to step outside his lake washington mansion for a bit of fun but whats got everyone talking isnt just the snowits the sheer oddity of seeing one of the worlds richest men in such a carefree almost goofy light  

the video short and simple has sparked a whirlwind of reactions online some call it cringeworthy questioning why a man known for tackling global crises is suddenly tossing snowballs others find it endearing a humanizing peek behind the billionaire curtain posted in late february 2025 its a stark contrast to gates typical contentthink climate change solutions and vaccine advocacymaking this snowy detour all the more jarring was it a calculated pr move to seem relatable or just a spontaneous moment from a guy whos spent decades under the spotlight x users are split with memes and hot takes flying as fast as the flurries themselves  

seattles recent weather backs up the timingearly february brought enough snow to snarl garbage pickup and close a few roads a novelty in the rainy pacific northwest gates whos lived in the region since his microsoft days clearly didnt let it pass him by whether you see it as awkward charming or just plain weird this snow day stunt has given us a rare unscripted look at a man who usually plays it straight dive into the reactions the context and the speculationwhat does bill gates frolicking in the snow really mean watch the breakdown and join the conversation below

title: serving dmca counternotices when amazon sellers are suspended for copyright claims in 2021
description:
jacques lavaud here four count them one two three four four wins last week and today im going to be talking to you about one of those wins where a client was suspended after receiving a copyright complaint and how he got that seller reinstated so number one you can always file a counternotice when you receive a copyright complaint its all under a body of law called a digital millennium copyright act and by serving a counternotice or having us as your lawyer serve a counternotice youre telling whoever made that complaint that they can either put up or shut up they can either sue you or the complaint goes away and more often than not theyre not going to file that lawsuit

number two what jacques found to be effective is putting in the plan of action a decision by the seller to stop selling that particular product now does that get the complaint off your account i dont think it does but for jacques and this particular seller that resulted in what the seller needed which is to get back to selling because that particular product was relatively meaningless to his account so with amazon theres almost always multiple ways to skin the cat so copyright complaints counternotices stop selling the product get a retraction of the complaint theres a lot of different things that we do to help you get reinstated and if you want to learn more you can call text email me or submit your case at amazonsellerslawyercom

in this tutorial ill guide you through the process of removing copyright claims from your youtube videos when youve used music from pixabay well also cover how to find the license for the music and file a dispute if necessary

have you ever faced the frustrating situation of receiving a copyright claim on your video even though you used music from a supposedly copyrightfree source like pixabay dont worry youre not alone in this video ill share my stepbystep method to help you resolve this issue and get your video back on track

first well dive into the reasons behind copyright claims and how they can occur especially when using music from platforms like pixabay understanding the content id system and how it works will give you valuable insights into the process

next ill walk you through the process of finding the license for the pixabay music you used in your video this is an essential step to gather the necessary evidence to support your dispute ill show you where to locate the license information and how to ensure you have all the required details

once you have the license information well move on to the dispute process ill provide you with effective strategies and tips to craft a compelling dispute that increases your chances of success well discuss the key elements to include in your dispute and how to present your case convincingly

throughout the video ill share reallife examples and success stories from creators who have successfully resolved copyright claims related to pixabay music their experiences will inspire and motivate you to take action and protect your content

by the end of this tutorial youll have a clear understanding of how to remove copyright claims find the license for pixabay music and file a dispute effectively youll regain control over your videos and continue sharing your valuable content with confidence

title: are memes legal as fair use
description:
httpwwwattorneystevecom  yes its okay to share our videos

need a fair use opinion letter from an ip lawyer  fill out this form and send it in for a quote  httpswwwscribdcomdocument473424267legalfairuseopinionletterquoteform

are memes legal

this is not always an easy question to answer  as a copyright fair use lawyer it depends on the material you are using and what you are creating  it can also depend on how you are using the meme

in particular we ask about the app mematic which is an iphone application i recently downloaded on my iphone  i bought the pro version which cost more and i posted a few meme posts on my instagram account  

today i found a popup message on my phone that alerted me that there could be thirdparty copyright at issue and directed me to the mematic terms of use see below  in reviewing the terms they state their service is for personal use only and that the meme photos are as is

this is why it is important to always check the terms of service before assuming you have a legal right to make commercial use out of photos or video memes

that being said there is a concept known as fair use which is a statutory right to use photos and video clips for comment and criticism parody and for transformative use purposes  this means when you add new meaning and expression to a photo or video  fair use is probably the most important legal doctrine that would make the use of memes legal but you must keep in mind there is a fourfactor test that has to be satisfied

also considering whether memes are legal or not one should also consider more than just copyright infringement  5 other causes of action could arise as well when considering memes

1  defamation libel  false statements in memes
2  invasion of privacy  a using a meme that invades the privacy of another or b publicizes private facts or c memes which place persons in a false light 
3  right of publicity  using a photo of a person without their consent on a commercial website

watch these privacy videos for more information about the above torts under california law
  
1 false light  httpsyoutubexob0twinu8
2  publication of private facts  httpsyoutubem3m2oiyni2o
3  right of publicity  httpsyoutubeelmfe5zn5ra
4  invasion of privacy private affairs  httpsyoutubedbjowgc3sve

make sure to subscribe to our legal channel to get more updates on fair use

mematic terms of use

this app may display include or make available content including images videos gifs and other data and information that may be subject to copyright and other intellectual property rights under the law this content is provided to you as is for your information and personal use only you use this content at your own risk and discretion

hope you enjoyed this video  dont forget to watch this video that talks about a case where a meme lawsuit was filed and the plaintiff won a 150k judgment following a jury verdict

title: actual damages in copyright infringement law explained by attorney steve
description:
httpwwwvondranlegalcom  dont forget to subscribe

yes you can share our videos on your social media networks for noncommercial purposes  must provide attribution to the link above

in this episode of litigation whiteboard attorney steve discusses the legal concept of actual damages as it relates to copyright infringement law  this is not a tough concept and it falls under 17 usc 504b which states

b actual damages and profits

the copyright owner is entitled to recover the actual damages suffered by him or her as a result of the infringement and any profits of the infringer that are attributable to the infringement and are not taken into account in computing the actual damages in establishing the infringers profits the copyright owner must present proof only of the infringers gross revenue and the infringer must prove his or her deductible expenses and the elements of profit attributable to factors other than the copyrighted work

title: copyright claims and fair use an issue i have with amc

title: nfts copyright infringement  the dmca takedown
description:
in this episode of the daily creator we discuss what an artist can do if they find their work being used as an nft  artists are getting ripped off heres some answers if this happens to you

the current copyight act was written in 1976  the digital millennium copyright act was written in 1998  it is now 2022 neither of these pieces of legislation can really be said to have kept up with the times  if you are an artist and you believe that your work has been wrongfully copied in an nft you still need to follow the rules  this means submitting a takedown notice to the platform  

here is the link to the openseaio takedown notice

httpssupportopenseaiohcenusarticles4412092785043whatcanidoifmyartimageorotheripisbeingsoldwithoutmypermission

httpsairtablecomshrgfp1znwxhxwjrt


if you do think that you that you have been infringed submit a takedown notice on the platform  if it is not taken down you may want to contact an attorney  

eric farber is the founder and ceo of creators legal the worlds first diy platform for content creators  he is a former entertainment attorney that represented the tupac shakur estate for over 18 years as well as hundreds of filmmakers musicians writers producers and a few hundred proathletes  he is the bestselling author of the case for culture about growing your business through culture  

wwwcreatorslegalcom

title: dacs explains an introduction to copyright infringement
description:
dacs digital communications executive gives a brief introduction to copyright infringement

copyright is infringed when someone carries out one of the copyright owners exclusive rights without their permission and an exception to copyright does not apply

this can be in relation to the whole or a substantial part of the artistic work what is substantial is determined by a qualitative test not a quantitative one which means that there may be an infringement even if a small but distinctive portion of the original artwork is copied



about dacs
established by artists for artists dacs is a notforprofit visual artists rights management organisation passionate about transforming the financial landscape for visual artists through innovative new products and services we act as a trusted broker for 100000 artists worldwide founded over 30 years ago dacs is a flagship organisation that campaigns for artists rights championing their sustained and vital contribution to the creative economy we collect and distribute royalties to visual artists and their estates through payback artists resale right copyright licensing and artimage since we were founded in 1984 we have paid over 100 million in royalties to artists and their estates  a significant source of income supporting artists livelihoods their practice and legacy

you are authorised to act on behalf of the owner of an exclusive right that is allegedly infringed and acknowledge that any person who knowingly materially misrepresents that material or activity is infringing may be subject to liability for damages

title: what is copyright and fair use policy  youtube copyright policy malayalam
description:
the complete right on an original work by its real owner is called copyright the rightful owner is vested with all kinds of legal rights hence the content cannot be distributed copied manipulated or used in any form either for commercial or nonprofit purposes without the consent of the owner copyright is applicable for various audiovisual contents like tv programs movies and online videos all kinds of sound recordings also have copyright text contents and visual arts like painting posters etc are also included as all we know the computer softwareapp and video games are included too

the fair use policy is the most misinterpreted terminology in connection with copyright the definition of fair use varies in different countries according to their copyright laws but in common if we use original content for reporting news or making critical analysis or for the commentary it can come under fair use practice any type of commercial use cannot be considered as fair use the purpose and the type used the nature of copyrighted work amount and importance of copied content etc determines the fair use practice the profitability and the potential market of the original owner should not be affected if the use is considered fair use

title: copyright infringement on images
description:
copyright infringement on images

welcome to expert answers

this is a question we get asked a lot

i have received a bill from gettycorbis images for using one of their images without permission what should i do

when you go onto google images and you see all these wonderful pictures has it ever occurred to you to who owns them

well invariably someone does  not all those images are in the public domain   and you if you take an image off the internet and you use it in your book or your publication or on your website very often what will happen is you will get a big fat juicy bill in the post from whoever owns the image wanting the licence fee for using it 

nope google images is not public domain  

if you find that youve used this image  

then i understand that there is one pixel in these images which the image company is sticking in there purposely so they can identify the images on the internet 

they can identify whos using them and then they can send them the bill and typically the bill is going to be about seven hundred and fifty poundsvery often it is more 

so if youve used one of these images off of the internet and you havent paid the licence and you get a bill from the image copyright holder for seven hundred and fifty quid or there about or even more 

whatever you do dont ignore it because they will take you to court the good news is they will generally settle for a substantial amount less better not to go there in the first place

if youve got a problem where youve had a letter from someone who claims to own the copyright of an image because youve used an image that you got off of the internet somewhere you might want to take some legal advice

 expert answers legal advice in a click

title: submiting a copyright takedown request
description:
submit a copyright takedown request

if your copyrightprotected work was posted on youtube without authorization you can submit a copyright takedown request submitting a takedown request will start a legal process

before you submit a takedown request you should know

copyright exceptions you need to consider whether fair use fair dealing or a similar exception to copyright law applies if an exception applies then the takedown request you submit would be invalidpersonal info

if a video is removed for copyright infringement the name of the copyright owner will be visible on youtube in place of the videoif you give us a valid legal alternative such as the name of a company or authorized representative well review and apply it if appropriatethe copyright owner name you enter will become part of the public record of your request learn more about the public record of your takedown requestyour full legal name is required to complete a takedown request it may be shared with the uploader of the video removed for copyright infringementthe primary email address from your takedown request may be shared with the uploader of the video removed for copyright infringement the uploader might get in touch with you to resolve their copyright strikeyour physical address and phone number will remain confidential unless requested as part of a lawsuit if youtube is required to share any information well notify you before doing so

prevent copies you can select the option to prevent copies of the videos youre reporting from being reuploaded to youtube if you select this option your email address and copyright owner name may be shared with the user whose video is prevented from upload learn morescheduled requests you can schedule takedown requests to take effect after 7 days scheduled requests will notify the uploader and give them 7 days before the content gets removednonvideo content if you want to submit a takedown request for nonvideo content such as channel icon images follow the steps outlined here our webform doesnt support nonvideo takedown requests

how to submit a takedown request

the fastest and simplest way to submit a copyright takedown request is to fill out our webform on a computer the copyright owner or agent authorized to act on the owners behalf should submit the request

do not make false claims misuse of the takedown webform such as submitting false information may result in the suspension of your account or other legal consequences

click this button to go to the webform

submit a copyright takedown request

you can also access the webform directly from youtube studio

sign in to youtube studiofrom the left menu click copyrightclick new removal request

we also accept copyright takedown requests by email fax and mail learn more

track your takedown requests

to view the copyright takedown requests youve previously submitted to youtube

sign in to youtube studiofrom the left menu click copyrightclick removal requests

manage all your copyrightprotected content

if you manage many copyrightedprotected works and often need to submit copyright takedown requests you may be eligible for our more advanced copyright management tools learn more about youtubes copyright management tools

title: learn about the copyright claims board an asmp tala and copyright alliance panel
description:
on may 16 the copyright alliance and texas accountants and lawyers for the arts tala in partnership with the american society of media photographers asmp hosted a panel titled learn about the copyright claims board the copyright claims board or ccb is an alternative forum to federal court to resolve certain small copyright disputes

with the ccb due to launch before the end of june the panel is designed to provide parties with information they will need to know to bring and defend cases before the ccb the panel will walk attendees through each step of the ccb process from filing a case with the ccb through the final decision

our expert panelists including a ccb officer and the ccb supervisory copyright claims attorney from the us copyright office will answer these questions and more during the event panelists include

david carson copyright claims officer us copyright office

whitney levandusky supervisory copyright claims attorney copyright claims board us copyright office

thomas maddrey asmp general counsel  head of national content and education

terrica carrington vice president of legal policy and copyright counsel copyright alliance

keith kupferschmid ceo copyright alliance panel moderator

whether you are considering bringing a case before the ccb or just interested in finding out more about this groundbreaking new tribunal at the us copyright office check out this excellent panel discussion

get ready for a tech blunder thats igniting a firestorm as of february 25 2025 apples voicetotext feature on iphones has stumbled into a wild controversy say racist and for a fleeting moment trump flashes on the screen before it corrects itself users are livid with cries of whoever at apple did this should lose their job echoing across social media i tested it myself on my iphonespoke racist loud and clear and sure enough trump popped up like an uninvited guest its not just a quirky glitch its a lightning rod especially with donald trump back in the white house since january 20th pushing his agenda hard

a dmca takedown request is a written notification sent to an online service provider such as a web host or search engine informing them that infringing content has been posted on their service 

the dmca is a us copyright law that provides protection to copyright owners by allowing them to take action against online service providers who host infringing content to tackle a dmca takedown request the service provider must take action to remove or disable the infringing content in order to avoid potential legal action

while this is a great first step if you are concerned about someone stealing your music there are a few steps you can take to protect your copyright first and foremost make sure that you properly copyright your music in the united states you can do this by registering your music with the us copyright office this will give you legal protection and allow you to take legal action if someone steals your music

once your music is copyrighted it is a good idea to include a copyright notice on any recordings or performances of your music this can be as simple as including the copyright symbol  the year of publication and your name on the recording or performance

additionally you can use a watermark or digital fingerprint on your recordings to identify them as yours and make it more difficult for someone to steal your music without being detected you can also use a licensing platform such as ascap or bmi to manage and track the use of your music and ensure that you are being properly compensated for its use

it is also important to be cautious about sharing your music online when sharing your music on social media or other online platforms consider using privacy settings to control who can access your music and how it can be used you can also use a licensing platform to manage the rights to your music and track its use online

title: youtube copyright claims filter feature  remove claimed content from videos
description:
theyre currently rolling out 2 changes to the video copyright details page

01 page design weve updated the layout of the page if youre looking for the claimants name and claim policy details hover over the impact on the video row

02 copyright tab on a videos details page we added a new copyright tab so you can easily access copyright info from any videos details page

remember that the information and options for responding to claims havent changed

if your video has a content id claim it may be restricted from being viewed or monetized in certain places you can edit out the claimed content without having to upload a new video to remove the claim and the associated restrictions

if completed successfully any of the following options will automatically remove a content id claim

 trimout segment you can edit your video to remove only the claimed segment

 replace song if the audio in your video has been claimed you may be able to replace it with music from the youtube audio library

 mute song if the audio in your video has been claimed you may be able to mute it you can choose to mute only the song or all of the audio in the video

trim replace or mute claimed content

to remove claimed content from a video

01 sign in to youtube studio
02 from the left menu select content
03 click the filter bar and then copyright claims
04 find the video youre interested in
05 in the restrictions column hover over the copyright claim
06 click see details
07 under the content identified in this video section find the relevant claim and click the actions threedot menu vertical and then trim out the segment replace song or mute song


trim out segment
this option allows you to remove the segment of your video that received the content id claim

01 optional edit the start time and end time of the section youre removing
      keep in mind that if some claimed content stays in your video the claim wont be removed
02 click continue and then trim

the content id claim will be removed from your video once all claimed content has been trimmed

replace song audio claims only

this option allows you to replace claimed audio with audio from the youtube audio library

01 use the search filters  to find a new audio track click play  to preview tracks

02 when you find a song you like click the add button the song will be displayed in a blue box in the editor
    click and drag the box to change when the song should start remember that if some claimed audio remains in your video the claim will not be removed
    drag the boxs edges to adjust the amount of music that plays
    use the zoom options zoom in for more precise edits

03 optional add more tracks

04 click save and then replace

the content id claim will be removed from your video once all claimed audio has been fully replaced

mute song audio claims only
this option lets you mute the claimed audio in your video you can choose to mute only the song or all of the audio in the video

01 choose how youd like to mute
       mute all sounds when the song plays
          during the claimed audio portion of the video all audio is muted
          this option is usually faster and more likely to remove the claim automatically
       the mute song only beta
          mutes are just the claimed song other audio such as dialogue or sound effects will not be muted
          this edit usually takes longer and may fail if the song is difficult to remove

02 edit the start and end times of the audio mute optional
       remember that if some claimed audio remains in your video the claim will not be removed

03 preview the edit in the video player 

04 click continue and then mute the edit will start processing

the content id claim will be removed from your video if all claimed audio can be muted

update on february 7 2018 2 more copyright claims

1 month ago sony music entertainment made a bogus copyright claim on this video

for free and uncensored discussion visit httpsforumwebseodesignerscom

sme claimed that it contains a part of their song count down planet 13  wednesday 13s frankenstein drag queens httpswwwyoutubecomwatchvymxjg8ldlkc that was recorded in 1996

in reality the sound effect was taken from madacy music group royaltyfree cd called 100 sound effects vol 1 this cd was copyrighted in 1993 and sold in 19941995

after disputing their initial copyright claim based on the broken automatic content id detection sme replied

after reviewing your dispute sme has decided that their copyright claim is still valid
video title polynesian fertility chant
copyrighted content count down planet 13
claimed by sme

it was only our appeal that forced them to withdraw their bogus claim one month later

good news after reviewing your dispute sme has decided to release their copyright claim on your youtube video

on december 10 2017 this video received 2 more bogus copyright claims from the orchard music and believe music both infringing the original madacy group copyright

pachamama  el espiritu de la tierra claimed by believe music

ceremony of the seventh circle studio claimed by the orchard music

their original pieces had both been created years after the royaltyfree madacy music group release using the very same sound clip

on january 11 2018 believe music released their claim

on february 6 2018 the orchard music released their claim

dont let sony music entertainment and other copyright mobsters bully and extort you spread the word on this case and make sure to appeal if you need any help we are happy to help

title: the trade secrets secrets of intellectual property  what is copyright infringement
description:
an interview by dan kennedy with seattle attorney timothy b mccormack founder of mccormack intellectual property law ps 

the dont copy this aka the trade secrets of intellectual property online book  video series is an online creative commons law online book and video series by attorney timothy b mccormack the founder of seattle based intellectual property law firm mccormack intellectual property law ps the trade secrets of intellectual property or dont copy this online book series is divided into chapters that will be fully published as a book when done 

intellectual properties are one of these issues that touch everybody this series is designed to help bring light to what law is and how it works 

dan kennedy why should people care about copyrights

timothy b mccormack copyrights are important because they help to drive the economy they help to incentivize artist and photographers some of them risk their lives to bring us images from the war zone or document human right atrocities look at the founding fathers wrote copyrights into the constitution itself today intellectual property is the states second largest export copyrights are a really big deal  

dan kennedy wow so what exactly is a copyright

timothy b mccormack a copyright is a legal property right one has in photographs art books music and artistic work there are six exclusive copyrights and the most famous of which is the right to prevent other people from making a copy of your work without your permission 

dan kennedy if you write a book or create an image do you own it forever 

timothy b mccormack if you write a book or take a picture you do not own it forever you own it for your life plus 70 years for your eras corporations are a flat 100 years

dan kennedy what happens when photograph copyright expires

timothy b mccormack if a photograph or book or painting is not in the public domain its copyrighted the general rule is if you didnt create it you cant use it now there are exceptions this video for example is going to be licensed under which is called creative commons that means you can copy it you can distribute it you can use it for educational purposes  you cant use it for commercial you got to give attributions and you cant change it damages for unauthorized use of copyrights can be pretty stiff up to 150000 per infringement so for example unwillful infringement of ten images equals 15 million dollars

if a strike is issued well let you know by email through notifications on mobile and desktop and in your channel settings well also tell you

what content was removed

which policies it violated for example adult content or violence

how it affects your channel

what you can do next

if your content violates our community guidelines heres how it affects your channel

warning

we understand mistakes happen and you dont mean to violate our policies  thats why the first violation is usually only a warning note that youll only be warned once and this warning will remain on your channel the next time your content is found to violate the community guidelines youll get a strike in some cases a single case of severe abuse will result in channel termination without warning if you think we made a mistake you can appeal the warning

first strike

if we find your content doesnt follow our policies for a second time youll get a strike

this means you wont be able to do the following for one week

upload videos live streams or stories

create custom thumbnails or community posts

created edit or add collaborators to playlists

add or remove playlists from the watch page using the save button

full privileges will be restored automatically after the 1week period but your strike will remain on your channel for 90 days

second strike

if you get a second strike within the same 90day period as your first strike you will not be able to post content for 2 weeks if there are no further issues full privileges will be restored automatically after the 2week period but each strike expires 90 days from the time it was issued

third strike

three strikes in the same 90day period will result in your channel being permanently removed from youtube also note that each strike expires in 90 days from the time its issued and that deleting the content will not remove your strike

title: copyright claims on youtube how to not get copyrighted explained
description:
copyright claims on youtube how to not get copyrighted explained and how not to fall foul of the youtube community guidelines plus best practices every youtube creator needs to know to keep your channel claimfree avoid demonetization or worse still channel termination without warning

the community guidelines cover everything you do on youtube not just video uploads this includes shorts comments you post and even your thumbnail images if you do violate any of these rules the response can range from suspending a creators privileges all the way to account termination

taking it a step further if you want to monetize make money from your channel there are a few more things to understand like the youtube partner program policies and the advertiserfriendly guidelines

the best way to avoid getting warnings or strikes is to make sure you always follow the community guidelines and when you upload your videos to youtube make them unlisted or private this way you can take advantage of the copyright and ad suitability checks carried out for you by youtube during the upload process having your video set to either of these means that you can address any issues before your video actually goes public

title: cube computer channel video microstopped by microsoft dmca takedown
description:
as of october 14 2014 a company called marketly working on behalf of microsoft is issuing takedown notices on youtube videos according to geekwire microsoft cited that the reasoning for this is due to product keys embedded in the comments not the videos themselves in question i think the company working on behalf of microsoft is getting a bit trigger happy with the dmca gun heres my reasoning on this

1 the copyright infringement notification tool on youtube is intended to be used to remove videos from the site when the video material contains content from the copyright holder used in an infringing matter is not used in a matter that is considered a fair use under copyright law and

2 issuing takedown notices on noninfringing videos just because some of them may have product keys embedded in the comments is a clear abuse of the system there are ways of solving the problem with comments other than punishing the uploader for it

a cube computer channel video has been targeted today by this abuse of the dmca

the video httpswwwyoutubecomwatchvlfjcr16ybtm
activation of windows 7 family pack using the telephone option
is merely a sub 10min video discussing how to telephone activate a pc with a windows 7 home premium family pack license no product keys were disclosed in the video in fact most of the time the camera is facing me and not at the computer screen this is a fine example of dmca abuse also no windows product keys were posted in the comments if they were they would have been removed since part 6 of the comments policy prohibits this to begin with

heres the geekwire article mentioned earlier
httpwwwgeekwirecom2014microsoftissuingtakedownnoticesyoutubevideoscontainingwindowsrelatedcontent


when posting comments please abide by the appropriate comments policy more info at the link below
httpwwwfacebookcomnotescubecomputercompanycubecomputerchannelappropriateyoutubecommentspolicy443253722390844

title: msnbc fires joy reid
description:
joy reid finally fired msnbc axes the hatespewing harpy of the left

well folks its a day conservativesand honestly anyone with a shred of common sensehave been waiting for joy reid has been booted from msnbc the network finally pulled the plug on the reidout in a longoverdue shakeup and the timing couldnt be sweeterfebruary 2025 just as the nations enjoying a fresh batch of sanity after years of her venomous rants this wasnt just about low ratings though advertisers clearly werent lining up to sponsor her hour of misery it was about reids relentless mission to stir hate not just toward maga folks but americans in general for years shes been the poster child for divisive drivel slinging insults like a malfunctioning mud cannoncalling trump supporters racist nazis accusing everyday patriots of worshipping power over principle and even smearing the country itself with her sanctimonious bile  

the news broke on february 23 2025 and x lit up like a fourth of july barbecue with reactions from gleeful conservatives and fedup viewers posts on x hailed it as karma for her hate and racism with one user quipping turns out calling half the country deplorable every night doesnt keep the lights on another called it long overdue pointing to her cringeinducing thanksgiving tirades and wild claims about reparations for white people reids schtick wasnt just antimagait was antiamerican painting anyone who didnt nod along to her farleft gospel as backward bigots her final episode airs this week and good riddance msnbcs new prez rebecca kutler is swapping her slot for a trio from the weekend hoping to scrub the stench of reids reign  


lets be real this firings been brewing since her unhinged rants alienated even the bluest of blue viewers from her 2017 homophobic blog post scandal which she dodged with a hacker excuse to her recent meltdowns over trumps return reids been a onewoman wrecking ball of credibility conservatives on x are popping champagne with sentiments like good riddance to the mentally obnoxious racist echoing loud and clear liberals might cry foul but when youve spent years demonizing your own countrymenred blue or otherwiseits no shock the axe finally fell so long joymaybe now you can take up a quieter hobby like knitting sweaters for your cats check out the full scoop and join the roast below

title: when does copyright infringement become criminal
description:
httpwwwvondranlegalcom 



criminal copyright infringement explained by attorney steve

in this exciting episode of vondran legal hour attorney steve the copyright infringement attorney explains when infringement of movies music film video or photographs may become more than just a civil matter and may be something the fbi investigates and the united states department of justice may find an interest in prosecuting to seek restitution for victims and to send a message that willful copyright infringement will not be tolerated  this becomes even more possible when you have potential victims such as the mpaa or riia

there are a number of activities that can lead to a claim of criminal copyright infringement one of the most common is software piracy which is the unauthorized copying or distribution of software this can be done for a variety of reasons including financial gain or simply to make software more widely available another form of copyright infringement is the theft of tv signals this involves capturing and distributing copyrighted content without authorization from the rights holders this is often done in order to make content available to people who would not otherwise have access to it while both software piracy and theft of tv signals are illegal they can also lead to civil liability if someone is found to be infringing on someone elses copyright

title: rant against false copyright claims
description:
this has gone on for too long

excerpts from actual us copyright laws
dmca title ii the online copyright infringement liability limitation act ocilla creates a safe harbor for online service providers osps including isps against copyright liability if they adhere to and qualify for certain prescribed safe harbor guidelines and promptly block access to allegedly infringing material or remove such material from their systems if they receive a notification claiming infringement from a copyright holder or the copyright holders agent ocilla also includes a counternotification provision that offers osps a safe harbor from liability to their users upon notice from such users claiming that the material in question is not in fact infringing

under section 107 the fair use of a copyrighted work is not copyright infringement even if such use technically violates section 106 while fair use explicitly applies to use of copyrighted work for criticism news reporting teaching scholarship or research purposes the defense is not limited to these areas

section 106 granted five exclusive rights to copyright holders

   1 the right to reproduce copy
   2 the right to create derivative works of the original work
   3 the right to sell lease or rent copies of the work to the public
   4 the right to perform the work publicly if the work is a literary musical dramatic choreographic pantomime motion picture or other audiovisual work and
   5 the right to display the work publicly if the work is a literary musical dramatic choreographic pantomime pictorial graphic sculptural motion picture or other audiovisual work

title: youtubes copyright policy  copyright infringement  swarit advisors
description:
nowadays youtube has become one of the biggest videosharing platforms in the world as youtube increases the number of creators also increases all around the world you should know that youtube takes copyrightinfringement very seriously and a video claimed to be violating the actual owners copyright is usually taken down or blocked if an individual publishes a video created by someone else without valid permission or license then he is liable to copyright infringement youtube doesnt allow any user to use the content of the original owner

there are two main reasons to take down or block a published video

first one is takedown action this action occurs when an infringer uploads content or video of an original creator without any permission or license the actual creator can file a takedown notice through the platform this notice is a legal notice regulated by the principles of law after filing the notice youtube examines the notice and takes down the content if it is satisfied that the infringer has violated the owners rights 

second is mismatch of content id youtube also developed a unique tool which is known as content id youtube grants a unique contentid for videos to the owners of copyright whenever a video is published on youtube the algorithm of youtube checks whether the video or audio uploaded is similar to the millions of those published to youtube if the uploaded video matches youtube by itself files a copyright claim for the owner releasing the owner to take action by himself

so what can a youtuber do when someone else copies your content

if the content id of youtube fails to recognize the copying content of an original creator then a youtuber can file a report for the duplication
first you have to click the report video option found in the video that is claimed to be violating your right and then select the option infringes my rights and click on the option shown as infringes my copyrights
once you ensure that you hold the rights for the content and if the content usage doesnt come under fair use then a takedown notice can be made by filing a web form given by the platform click on the submit copyright compliant button 

after that you have to state the party affected by the infringement and paste the violating video link and original video link youtube gives an option to add more videos in case you find more than one copied video
to file a complaint under the dmca or digitalmillenniumcopyrightact you have to give your personal information like your name address contact numbers email id etc also you have to submit a declaration stating that the notice made is

 in excellent faith 
 correct 
 the party is informed about the legal ramifications in the case of a false notification 
 usage of content is not allowed by the actual copyright owner 
 the complainant is the actual owner or certified agent who can act upon the violation of such rights

after the above step youtube will mail you regarding the take down requests authentication and inform the opposite party regarding the complaint filed against him

what can you do when your video is removed for copyright infringement
well you can resort to these two remedies

first is filing a counternotice  when an owner files a takedown notice for publishing a video on youtube without the owners approval youtube takes down the video but the opposite party can file a counternotification for restoring the takedown video this notification can be filed when the party confirms that their use of the content falls under the fair use policy or if there is misrecognition of content by the owner 

second is challenging a content id claim a youtube creator whose video has been found similar to the existing content can challenge such claim
1if the content was unidentified 
2if its your original content 
3if the creator has valid licenses or certification to such content
4if the usage of content comes under fair use or dealing

support the claim release the claimtakedown your video 

it can be fairly said the youtubecopyrightpolicy is strict and restrictive every content creator who wants to take benefits of youtubes massive audience must be well aware of youtubes copyright policy since an infringement case is quite a costly affair

title: disputing copyright claims of smartsound music on youtube update 2020
description:
if you upload your videos to youtube you may sometimes see a copyright notice from another company when using smartsound music this can happen because some smartsound music is licensed on a nonexclusive basis from some of the top composers in the industry these composers may also be selling the same music through other avenues that are not royaltyfree according to youtubes regulations only music that is 100 exclusively owned is allowed to be uploaded into their content id system however in practice this is not regulated and other companies that may also represent the music to some degree will uploaded it into content id the music is then matched and causes a false copyright claim

if you purchased the music from smartsound then it is properly licensed for use in monetized youtube videos and you should dispute the claim 

first go to your youtube studio and select videos in the sidebar and find the video that has a copyright claim listed you can use the filter copyright claims to find the affected video more quickly

hover above the copyright claim restriction of the video in the center of the screen then click on see details here you will see how the copyright strike currently affects your video in the bottom right you will see a button that says select action to dispute your claim click on it and in the dropdown menu choose dispute

first you need to confirm that your claim is proper and not a misunderstanding as you have purchase to the music from smartsound you can check the checkbox my dispute isnt based on any of the reasons above i would still like to dispute this content id claim in the radio button menu choose the option license and click continue

click the the checkbox i have permission to use the content from the copyright owner and click continue in the text box provide rationale simply enter smartsound or licensed from smartsoundtick all three of the following checkboxes and enter your full name in the signature field review that everything is entered correctly then click on submit

with the dispute active any revenue the video earns that will go into an escrow account and as soon as that dispute is released the money will all come back to the creator in some cases it may be a good idea to post your video initially as private in order to preemptively deal with any false claims before making the video public to do this when uploading a video select the private visibility option in the final step of creating the video even though only you can watch it at this point the videos will still be checked for copyrighted content if copyrighted content is detected in the video you can still go through the previous steps while the video is set to private after the potential dispute is cleared you can release the video by changing it from private to public either in the video options or video dashboard

if you have any trouble getting the claim released or want to help expedite the process contact the claimant company directly you can check our faq section to find contact information for many of the companies that tissue these claims and they are typically prompt to release them when contacted 

unfortunately there is a little we can do from our end to stop other companies from improperly uploading non exclusive music into content id but by following these steps you should be able to quickly dispute any false copyright claims and get them released

title: dmca notice and takedown process

what is a dmca notice
a dmca notice is a copyright notice that you can use to take down material that you believe is infringing your intellectual property rights

what is the takedown process
the takedown process is the process by which you can request that a third party take down material that you believe is infringing your copyright

title: best of arijit singh mashup 2025  viniick  arijit
description:
disclaimer 

1 content ownership and licensing
music licensing any music played or posted on the channel must either be owned by the channel owner or licensed through a service such as a royaltyfree music provider or a licensing platform like bmi ascap or prs for music
original content if the music is created by the channel owner eg original bassline tracks the copyright is typically owned by the creator unless otherwise assigned or transferred
thirdparty content if using tracks created by others you must obtain proper licenses to avoid infringement if uploading content to platforms like youtube ensure you are either using content you own licensed content or content under creative commons
2 fair use guidelines
transformative work if you are remixing or sampling existing tracks you might argue that its a transformative work however even in cases of remixes or mashups the original copyright holder can still claim rights
fair use limitations fair use often applies to commentary criticism education or parody it can be risky to rely on fair use unless youre absolutely sure the work falls within this category
3 digital millennium copyright act dmca compliance
content id and claims on platforms like youtube content id matches copyrighted music against their database if you use copyrighted music the owner may claim your video or block it
take down notices copyright holders can issue a dmca takedown notice if their work is used without permission this can lead to the removal of content and potential penalties for the channel
counterclaims if you believe your content was removed unfairly you may issue a counterclaim but you should be confident that your content does not infringe copyright
4 monetization and revenue sharing
monetization rights channels may need permission from copyright owners to monetize music tracks this could involve splitting earnings with the rights holder if their content is used
revenue sharing many platforms like youtube use a revenuesharing model for copyrighted music the platform might allow monetization but give the revenue to the copyright holder
5 copyright infringement and penalties
infringement penalties unauthorized use of copyrighted music could result in penalties such as
removal of the content
loss of monetization
channel strikes on youtube
legal action from the copyright holder
preventive measures ensure that all music used is licensed or falls under fair use if applicable to avoid these penalties
6 creative commons and royaltyfree music
using creative commons music licensed under creative commons can often be used freely but its important to follow the terms of the license which may include giving proper credit not using it commercially or not modifying the work
royaltyfree music platforms like artlist epidemic sound or audiojungle offer royaltyfree music that can be used without worrying about copyright as long as you comply with their licensing terms
7 attribution and credits
giving credit if youre using tracks under creative commons or other types of licenses requiring attribution you must provide proper credits in the video description or as stipulated in the license terms
attribution example music provided by artist name under a creative commons license
8 creating a copyright policy for your channel
clear guidelines if youre running a channel its important to have clear terms for what content can be used and how this includes
whether others can remix or reuse your music
how you handle licensing requests for your own work
how you handle potential copyright violations from others

description:
what is copyright take down request  
if your copyrightprotected work was posted on youtube without authorization you can submit a copyright takedown request if you submit a take down request using our web form you can select the option to prevent copies of the videos from being uploaded again

selecting this option means youtube will make its best efforts to automatically prevent the videos youre requesting for removal from being reuploaded in the future keep in mind your takedown request must be found to be complete and valid before any videos are removed or prevented from reupload


note abuse of this feature may result in you losing the ability to use it for future takedown requests misuse of the webform such as submitting false information may result in the suspension of your account or other legal consequences


before selecting the prevent copies option make sure you own exclusive worldwide rights to the videos youre reporting in your takedown to select the prevent copies option


you can get to the webform from the copyright page of youtube studio in the removal requests tab click new removal request


if you selected prevent copies on your takedown request and your takedown is approved you can see how many copies have been automatically prevented from reupload

sign in to youtube studio
from the left menu select copyright 
click the removal requests tab
click a row the row expands to show more details about the video requested for removal
in the automatically prevented column you can find the number of videos that have been automatically prevented from reupload
when the status of this column is active it means youtube is actively making its best efforts to prevent others from reuploading these videos


turn off the option
if you selected prevent copies on your takedown request you can turn off the feature at any time turning it off will allow any future copies of the removed videos to be uploaded to turn off the option

sign in to youtube studio
from the left menu select copyright 
click the removal requests tab
click a row the row expands to show more details about the video requested for removal
uncheck the box next to prevent copies

title: copyright infringement  what if someone infringes your copyright
description:
what should you do if you are a victim of copyright infringement what can you do if your novel blog post photograph or song is used by another without permission

lets say someone copies or publishes your article or photograph or something substantially similar to it without your permission is that copyright infringement according to title 17 of the united states code also known as the copyright act the answer is yes

infringement occurs when a person copies distributes performs or displays all or part of a copyrighted work  or in television conducts a secondary transmission of a cable program without the consent of the cable system owner 

once you register your copyright with the us copyright office you can sue that person in federal court if you can prove infringement  either by getting the infringer to admit his guilt or by showing that he had access to your copyrighted work and that his material is the same or substantially similar to yours   then you can recover monetary damages and lost profits if someone willingly infringes your copyrighted work they may also face criminal penalties  up to five years in prison for a first offense 10 years for a second

there are two ways to prove the substantial similarity of an infringing work one is to show fragmented literal similarity  meaning that the infringing work contains specific copied elements of your original work exact words melodies or lyrics for example the second type of similarity  called comprehensive nonliteral similarity  is more of a qualitative look and feel issue it is infringement if the structure of one work is substantially similar to another

title: remove fake copyright strike on youtube
description:
removing a fake copyright strike on youtube can be a frustrating experience but its important to follow the proper steps to resolve the issue here is a stepbystep guide on how to handle a fake copyright strike

understand youtubes copyright system familiarize yourself with youtubes copyright policies and guidelines this will help you understand the rules and processes involved in disputing a copyright strike

evaluate the strike carefully review the copyright strike notice and analyze its legitimacy consider whether the claim is valid or if it appears to be an erroneous or fraudulent claim

gather evidence if you believe the copyright strike is fake gather evidence to support your claim this could include timestamps video creation dates ownership proof and any other relevant information that proves you have the rights to use the disputed content

contact the claimant reach out to the claimant through youtubes messaging system or any other available contact information politely explain your position provide evidence and request that they retract the copyright strike

submit a dispute if the claimant does not respond or refuses to retract the copyright strike you can file a dispute with youtube to do this go to your youtube studio and navigate to the copyright section find the video in question and select the request retraction or dispute option follow the onscreen instructions and provide all relevant evidence to support your case

await response from the claimant after submitting the dispute youtube will notify the claimant and provide them with the evidence you presented the claimant then has a specified period usually 30 days to respond to your dispute

escalate the matter if the claimant fails to respond within the given time or refuses to retract the copyright strike you can escalate the issue by appealing the decision youtube provides an appeals process where you can further explain your case and provide additional evidence

seek legal advice if necessary in some cases fake copyright strikes may require legal intervention if you believe the claimant is deliberately targeting you with fraudulent claims consult a lawyer specializing in copyright law to explore your options

remember its crucial to remain patient throughout this process resolving a fake copyright strike can take time but following the correct procedures increases your chances of successfully removing it

title: copyright infringement online
description:
copyright infringement  how to remove copyright infringement online

entcounsel is a law firm for creatives and entrepreneurs in the areas of social media law technology entertainment copyright and trademarks

step 1

attempt to reach out directly to the infringer first to remove the infringing content try and resolve

 

step 2

review the terms and conditions of the website posting the infringing material as they may have a procedure which may be dmca or notice and notice to remove the infringing content and provide you with a contact email

 

step 3

pursue social media reporting procedures for copyright infringement which may direct you to the us dmca or canadas notice and notice procedures

most social media sites have copyright infringement reporting procedures

for facebook fill out their online copyright infringement form at

httpswwwfacebookcomhelpcontact
937027619679465

for twitter report copyright infringement by submitting a copyright report at
httpssupporttwittercomformsdmca

for instagram report copyright infringement by submitting a copyright report form at
httpshelpinstagramcomcontact539946876093520

for youtube you can submit a copyright takedown notice via their webform at
httpssupportgooglecomyoutubeanswer2807622hlen

for pinterest you can submit a copyright infringement notification via their online form at

httpswwwpinterestcomaboutcopyrightdmcapin

step 4

ultimately you may have to report the copyright infringement via the dmca us or notice and notice canada procedures to have the copyright material removed

the dmca stands for the digital millennium copyright act incorporates two 1996 wipo treaties passed in 1998 it addresses copyright infringement online through title ii its online copyright infringement liability limitation act

it permits copyright owners to provide a notice in a prescribed form to an isp who forwards it to the website owner upon receipt of the dmca notice the allegedly infringing work must be taken down or blocked

provides a safe harbour for online service providers who are not liable and do not have to pay if they comply with the dmca notice and takedown regime

the website owner may provide a counternotice to the claimant which the isp must forward the counternotice provides a safe harbour to users when the material is not infringing and protects them from liability

if the claimant does not bring a lawsuit within a certain period then the alleged infringing content is put back up

a company must follow certain steps under the dmca 


the notice and notice protections for isps in canada are pursuant to s 4125 4126 and 41273 of the copyright modernization act 

the notice and notice system in canada is similar to the dmca takedown system in the us

in canada isps are legally required to pass notices of any allegations of copyright infringement to the website owner   they do not have to take the work down but just forward it

in the us the work must be taken down

an isp in canada has a safe harbour against them for copyright infringement provided they forward the notice

an isp or webhost is required to do the following

1forward any notices sent by copyright owners to the person who owns the website

2inform the copyright owner that the notice has been forwarded or if its not forwarded to explain why it was not forwarded

3the isp or webhost is still required to retain records of the notice for six months and one year if a lawsuit is commenced within that six month period in order to identify the alleged infringer

once an individual receives a notice the claimant still needs to obtain a court order to gain disclosure of their identity  they will then need to pursue formal legal proceedings to establish liability

the notice and notice requires that intermediaries such as internet service providers and web hosts forward notices of alleged copyright infringement as soon as feasible  if they dont then the copyright owner can pursue statutory damages against them in the amount of 5000 to 10000  the intermediaries must let the copyright owners know that the notice has been forwarded

the written notice must include information in the prescribed form

title: womans emotional walmart hire sparks dei debate
description:
tears and tattoos womans emotional walmart hire sparks debateis the retail giant that desperate

get ready for a story thats tugging at heartstrings and raising eyebrows all at once on february 24 2025 a woman uploaded a raw emotional video capturing her tearful reaction after landing a job at walmartface tattoos and all with more ink scrawled across her cheeks than signatures in a high school yearbook her hiring has folks buzzing is walmart so strapped for workers theyre throwing standards out the window the clip which dropped just hours ago shows her sobbing with gratitude a rare moment of vulnerability thats gone viral faster than you can say rollback prices but its not just feelgood vibestheres a bigger question lurking  

posts on x are lighting up with chatter about this hire some cheer walmarts shift toward inclusivity with one user noting tattoos dont define abilitygood for them focusing on personality others arent so sure snarking whats next hiring clowns with balloon animals the retail giants been loosening its dress code for yearsvisible tattoos got the green light back in 2021but face tattoos thats a bold leap with the us labor market still tight unemployment hovering at 42 in early 2025 walmarts not alone in casting a wider net a 2023 survey found 46 of employers now shrug off visible ink up from 27 a decade ago still this womans storytattooed writings plastered across her facepushes the envelope making you wonder is this a win for selfexpression or a sign of desperation  

her videos raw emotion hits hardshes not just celebrating a paycheck but a second chance x users speculate she mightve faced rejection elsewhere with one post musing bet shes got a story behind those tears critics though see it as walmart scraping the barrel with quips like more tattoos than a biker gangguess theyre hiring anyone now love it or hate it this moments sparking a culture clasholdschool norms versus a new era where inks just another accessory dive into the video the debate and the data belowis walmart leading a revolution or just hurting for help you decide

title: destiny 2 maker is frantically bemoaning youtubes takedown system
description:
earlier this month a bunch of destiny 2 youtube videos including some by high profile content makers and even bungie themselves were hit by rogue
destiny2 makerblasts youtube
destiny 2 maker blasts youtubes takedown system in wild lawsuit

earlier this month a bunch of destiny 2 youtube videos including some by high profile content makers and even bungie themselves were hit by rogue copyright takedown notices generated by fake google accounts bungie is now trying to sue the people responsible and has called out youtube for getting tricked by alleged sters in the first place

the destiny copyright takedown spree began earlier this month hitting soundtrack videos cutscenes and eventually other content including videos posted by bungie itself streamers with hundreds of thousands of subscribers like my name is byf and aztecross were hit as well leading to a minifreakout that bungie had changed its content maker guidelines which have traditionally been extremely lax

these actions are not being taken at the request of bungie or our partners the company wrote at the time to assuage players concerns please standby for future updates

bungie is now taking the matter to court to find out whos responsible for the rogue takedowns according to a new lawsuit filed march 25 and first reported by torrentfreak the complaint filed in the western district of washington targets up to 10 currently unidentified john does accused of using ulent dmca takedown notices to disrupt bungies community of players streamers and fans and causing bungie nearly incalculable damage

while the studio is still subpoenaing information to uncover the identities of the sters it says in the lawsuit it believes the rogue takedowns might have been retaliation for destiny soundtrack videos bungie had removed from youtube earlier in the month the ulent takedowns apparently began a day after the authorised ones were completed and used a fake gmail address that was very similar to the one used in those earlier takedowns

but wait it gets weirder according to the lawsuit at least one of the people seemingly responsible for the rogue takedowns apparently emailed some of the affected youtube accounts a manifesto explaining why if youre looking to place blame place it on youtube for its sloppy copyright takedown system and bungie for ignoring this issue for so long it reads

the lawsuit takes aim at youtubes overall system for copyright takedowns as well which bungie accuses of being easily gamed and hard to set right

bungie had to devote significant internal resources to addressing it and helping its players restore their vi

title: starlink introduces new tos with fair use policy  data cap coming for residential customers
description:
starlink has updated its terms of service tos which now references a new fair use policy that will go into effect next month

up until this point all starlink data has been unlimited  only differentiated between priority access and best effort depending on the particular service plan and where it was being used

but with congestion becoming an increasing problem starlink is moving to better balance supply and demand with some significant new limits on usage that will particularly impact heavy users

essentially spacex is acknowledging that starlink is a finite resource and that it is not possible to deliver truly unlimited data plans without performance dragging to a crawl in too many places to improve things spacex is moving towards network management practices similar to what is commonly seen in the cellular industry 

for the full story
httpswwwrvmobileinternetcomstarlinkintroducesnewtoswithfairusepolicydatacapcomingforresidentialcustomers

title: commentary  the nintendo creators program puts fair use and journalism at risk
description:
nintendo which has always been heavy handed in how it treats the use of its content on youtube has launched a new program to share revenue with creators that use the companys games in a video 

nintendo claims independent content with their gameplay footage as theirs and then denies the creator the right to earn revenue on that content ad revenue on those videos goes straight to nintendo  not to the creator that made the video in the first place including those who have a right to use that content

on the surface the new nintendo creators program sounds like a nice way to try and balance the issue for youtubers nintendo says theyll share 6070 of the revenue theyre taking with the creator but what it does instead is create a potentially dangerous precedent for journalism 

product reviews are fair use under us copyright law if a reviewer is evaluating a copyrighted work they have the right to display portions of that work in the course of that evaluation to have nintendo stake copyright claims on that content is wrong in the first place but now nintendo is going a step further by deciding which content can earn revenue and which cant so will they ever allow a critical review to earn revenue after the company claimed that video as their own doubtful 

this sets a dangerous precedent nintendo shouldnt be allowed to do what they have been doing especially with product reviews they should do what any good company would  respect the rights of creators and keep their hands out of the pockets of their fans

title: lawyer reacts to ai copyright claimed my last video  venus theory
description:
venus theory channel httpswwwyoutubecomvenustheory
in this lawyer reacts episode of the top music attorney podcast entertainment attorney miss krystle reacts to venus theorys video titled ai copyright claimed my last video and offers a lawyers perspective on the growing issue of aigenerated content and copyright claims the implications of aigenerated music and videos being falsely claimed are significant especially for creators across platforms like youtube miss krystle dives into the question of whether creators truly own the copyright to music made with ai tools and discusses the potential pitfalls this poses for artists musicians and content creators who rely on aigenerated content

also explored is the legal gray areas surrounding ai copyright and ownership as ai continues to evolve its crucial for creators to understand how these changes could affect their content and livelihoods the episode breaks down how easy it is for someone to falsely copyright claim aigenerated work and highlights the challenges that creators may face navigating the murky waters of copyright law in the digital age if youre a musician or content creator this is an essential watch to protect yourself from the aidriven copyright issues ahead
