title: joy reid finally fired from msnbc
description:
joy reid finally fired msnbc axes the hatespewing harpy of the left

well folks its a day conservativesand honestly anyone with a shred of common sensehave been waiting for joy reid has been booted from msnbc the network finally pulled the plug on the reidout in a longoverdue shakeup and the timing couldnt be sweeterfebruary 2025 just as the nations enjoying a fresh batch of sanity after years of her venomous rants this wasnt just about low ratings though advertisers clearly werent lining up to sponsor her hour of misery it was about reids relentless mission to stir hate not just toward maga folks but americans in general for years shes been the poster child for divisive drivel slinging insults like a malfunctioning mud cannoncalling trump supporters racist nazis accusing everyday patriots of worshipping power over principle and even smearing the country itself with her sanctimonious bile  

the news broke on february 23 2025 and x lit up like a fourth of july barbecue with reactions from gleeful conservatives and fedup viewers posts on x hailed it as karma for her hate and racism with one user quipping turns out calling half the country deplorable every night doesnt keep the lights on another called it long overdue pointing to her cringeinducing thanksgiving tirades and wild claims about reparations for white people reids schtick wasnt just antimagait was antiamerican painting anyone who didnt nod along to her farleft gospel as backward bigots her final episode airs this week and good riddance msnbcs new prez rebecca kutler is swapping her slot for a trio from the weekend hoping to scrub the stench of reids reign  


lets be real this firings been brewing since her unhinged rants alienated even the bluest of blue viewers from her 2017 homophobic blog post scandal which she dodged with a hacker excuse to her recent meltdowns over trumps return reids been a onewoman wrecking ball of credibility conservatives on x are popping champagne with sentiments like good riddance to the mentally obnoxious racist echoing loud and clear liberals might cry foul but when youve spent years demonizing your own countrymenred blue or otherwiseits no shock the axe finally fell so long joymaybe now you can take up a quieter hobby like knitting sweaters for your cats check out the full scoop and join the roast below

title: false copyright claims a corrupt system
description:
as many of you know youtubers like make a path presents ronny haze meg stansfield discussthedead ranting dead itshippychick and myself have all been experiencing an abuse of power on youtube involving fair use and copyright law with walking dead videos most of them are for simply using still images that are personally altered edited and reformatted by us as well ive discussed this in the past so i am focusing on another specific topic involving that with this video as a few of you know i have filed copyright claim disputes on all claimed videos many have told me that their disputes have been denied but mine havent been answered on yet a claimant can actually wait 30 days before the acceptance or denial option disappears and the claim is removed this means that no matter what circumstances a video is claimed for whether accurately or falsely claimed that claimant can still make money on a video by simply waiting out the 30 day period this can easily be abused and the fact that most videos get the most views and make the most money within the original time of the post is very important as well timesensitive videos like walking dead news videos can be claimed and almost no money can be made after the 30 day amount for the original content creator that worked hard on the video this is something i wanted to raise awareness on and bring to the surface because i believe it is important to think about i strongly believe that we should fight this issue to the best of our abilities raising awareness is one of the most important parts which is why i ask you to share this video and support it in addition to the other videos from ronny and megan i would like to say thank you for the support ahead of time because i know there are viewers out there who i am very grateful for that will help support us in this situation thank you for watching peace d

title: lawyer 1 copyright fair use myth you must know copyright law
description:
this video is about copyright law and copyright fair use  too many people fail to understand that fair use is a defense and is not something that can automatically protect you from a copyright infringement lawsuit 

im a copyright lawyer entertainment lawyer and fair use lawyer  some of my practice areas are
copyright law entertainment law fair use law youtube fair use law
 
subscribe to my channel for daily videos like this one and now you know if its true or false
in this video i discuss fair use  if you are a youtube creator you must learn as much as possible about fair use on youtube youtube fair use fair use youtube fair use copyright copyright fair use fair use rules fair use exception youtube fair use policy and fair use guidelines 

this video will help you to better understand what is fair use fair use right fair use exception and copyright fair use   

almost every single youtuber gets it wrong do you think if you say fair use you cant be sued for copyright infringement think again because you can certainly be sued even if you think what you did was fair use  fair use is a defense and its not something the person suing has to disprove fair use is a defense you must prove by arguing fair use you are basically saying even though i committed copyright infringement i should not have to pay damages because i had a valid excuse to use somebodys copyrighted work without their permission so fair use is a defense you must allege and prove its not something that can automatically insulate you from a copyright infringement lawsuit 

you must know what is fair use on youtube and you must be careful with fair use because youtubers often have the following issues movies fair use reaction videos fair use fair use movies fair use video game gaming fair use fair use meditation music fair use video clips gameplay fair use streaming fair use memes fair use fair use movies clips fair use short manga fair use transformative fair use fair use videos make videos with fair use mashup video fair use fair use beat fair use documentary fair use tiktok tiktok fair use karaoke fair use fair use content how to use music under fair use  fair use stock video in travel videos how does fair use work lawsuit fair use how fair use works fair use videos fair use violation copyright violation fair use duration copyright exceptions copyright claim fair use policy clips for fair use   
 
you dont want to find yourself in trouble because of fair use guidelines on youtube fair use youtube guidelines fair use request fair use disclaimer copyright dispute  fair use policy dispute copyright claim copyright strike youtube copyright strike copyright violation copyright infringement copyright claim or copyright lawsuit  there are no set rules about seconds fair use or fair use disclaimers 

i created this video to make sure youtube fair use explained fair use policy explained and you know how to make your videos fair use  you may find that a fair use copyright disclaimer is not enough

if youre looking to grow your channel to be a successful youtuber im ready im happy to assist you with your journey especially when you have a youtube problem to fix how do you contact youtube support to fix a problem

today if youre a youtube partner you can get email support which is awesome but what happens if you are accidentally demonetized now you are no longer a partner so no longer have email support what can you do

and not everyone has access to being a partner because of the one thousand subs four thousand hours requirement so what can you do your first options are to post your issue in the youtube help community ill share a link in the description and the experts in the community will do their best to assist you and you can contact at team youtube on twitter where staff are available to trouble shoot your issue  

my passion my skill what i love to do the most is help people fix problems ive been around youtube a long time youtube staff reached out to me to become a top contributor which is now the product expert program why should you care whats a product expert

product experts are passionate about sharing their knowledge product experts have direct contact to google employees and we get access to products before they are released ill share the link to this page in the description 

you put a lot of time and energy into making videos youtube is complex with lots of rules and they seem to always be changing further complicating things are all the new features  when something is borked something goes wrong or breaks what do you do this is where i come in my skill my expertise is understanding how youtube functions so i can help you solve the problem 

for example yesterday i heard about a creator having a monetization issue darrin was finding it impossible to get support he was having an issue with his adsense account and it caused his monetization to be disabled the monetization tab disappeared and he was stuck this morning his monetization is back his adsense is linked and he is good to go 

back a month or so brian woke up to his entire channel being demonetized with the reason of reused content this was obviously incorrect a mistake the difficulty there is no process available to appeal all that can be done is to wait the required thirty days and then reapply and hope the manual review goes well  as a gold product expert i was able to pass along the details to youtube staff and within fortyeight hours channel monetization was restored 

if you are having a problem i want to help you fix it i want to help you figure it out whatever it is  you should contact support first if you are a partner and have access you should try the help community and try team youtube on twitter if your problem isnt resolved to your satisfaction reach out to me

title: how to appeal copyright strikes on youtube  remove copyright claims
description:
how to appeal copyright strike on youtube 2018  how to remove copyright strikes on youtube videos by appealing copyright claims sometimes you get false content id claims or dinged with a copyright strike and you need to appeal under fair use or dispute a copyright claim against your videos

how to appeal community guideline strikes  httpsyoutubewyjm6mekzki live feb 24th

how to remove copyright strikes on youtube

make sure that you understand how fair use and the public domain work before you choose to dispute for either of those reasons youtube cant help you determine whether you should dispute a claim you may want to seek your own legal advice if youre not sure what to do

disputes are only intended for cases where you have all the necessary rights to the content in your video repeated or malicious abuse of the dispute process can result in penalties against your video or channel

how to dispute appeal or remove a copyright strike

 sign in to youtube
 in the top righthand corner click on your account icon
 click creator studio  video manager  copyright notices
 click the c symbol next to the video with the claim that you wish to dispute this will take you to information about whats been claimed in your video and who claimed it
 click file a dispute and fill in the appropriate fields to submit your dispute

title: the lofi girl copyright takedown controversy proves youtubes strike system is broken
description:
subscribe for daily pds news clips httpswwwyoutubecomcroguerocketsubconfirmation1
go to httpspubliccomdefranco and youll receive a free stock once you open an account and deposit this is a paid endorsement for open to the public member finra  sipc this is not advice investing involves risk of loss regulatory  firm fees apply
watch the full defranco news show httpswwwyoutubecomdefrancosubconfirmation1

in what can only be described as a tragedy the 28monthlong lofi girl music stream was officially taken down on sunday due to a series of false copyright strikes for those who dont know the channel its just a loop of a girl studying while lofi music plays and its insanely popular right the channel has nearly 11 million subs and just one of its streams had over 688 million views even the likes of will smith and cartoon network have ripped the concept off it seems that some company or group exploited what could be described as a loophole in youtubes dmca takedown procedures right as theres no real way to vet whether a claim is being issued in good faith or abusively to get a channel removed the channel was quick to act and decided to handle the situation in what creators have learned is the most effective method addressing it on twitter and tagging youtube this was a pretty clearcut case as lofi girl only plays music from its record label and music that it has the right to share and to its credit youtube was quick to respond and recognize the strikes were false and malicious saying confirmed the takedown requests were abusive  terminated the claimants account  weve resolved the strikes  reinstated your vids  it can sometimes take 2448 hours for everything to be back to normal so sorry this happened  thx for your patience as we sorted it out   and as of recording it looks like the streams are back up and running although it has to start back at zero however this has rubbed some people the wrong way lofi girl itself was frustrated that such a blatantly false claim was allowed through and that there is no reviewing process before strikes are issued writing were shocked and disappointed to see that theres still not any kind of protection or manual review of these false claims at the end of the day it was entirely out of our control and the sad part is that there was no way to appeal beforehandprevent it from happening 27 youtube is in a loselose situation here according to the dmca they cant intervene in copyright disputes based on the merits they can only intervene when its clearly a claim done for malicious reasons such as what happened here and theres an argument to be made that manually reviewing every claim the vast majority of which are legitimate claims is just not possible on the scale youtube operates but that scale also means that even if a small percentage of creators are hit its still a lot of people and they have no way to fight malicious or clearly fraudulent claims like take this creator who responded to youtubes tweet with i got copyright struck for rain in minecraft and you did nothing it has been over a month since your automated email told me that you would look into it

title: openai asks delhi court to reject publishers copyright claims in ai case
description:
just in openai is urging the delhi high court to dismiss a copyright plea filed by book publishers claiming that its ai model chatgpt does not use or reproduce content from original literary works according to recent court documents openai argues that the publishers led by the federation of indian publisherswhich includes industry giants like penguin random house and bloomsburyhave failed to substantiate their allegations the lawsuit is reportedly part of a broader global confrontation where various stakeholders including authors and media outlets are raising concerns about ai technologies using their works without proper permissions or licensing agreements 

were learning that the delhi high court is currently navigating these complex legal waters with separate proceedings urging media outlets to exercise restraint in reporting the details of the submissions openais legal representative sibal is reportedly pushing back against the federations claims citing procedural flaws including the lack of necessary authorization for filing the complaint this ongoing legal battle highlights a growing friction over the use of public data by ai technologies as openai calls for clarity on what constitutes fair use in this rapidly evolving landscape as the case unfolds it may set significant precedents for future litigation not only in india but across the globe

what we know so far is that the publishers remain determined to pursue their claims emphasizing the potential impact of ai on their business models as the delhi high court proceedings develop the outcomes could reshape the discourse surrounding copyright laws and ai applications stakeholders are watching closely as this case could have farreaching implications for how industries navigate the intersection of technology and intellectual property rights the world is waiting to see how these legal proceedings will unfold and what it might mean for the future of content creation in an aidriven world
